coneforest.psi.core

Interface PsiAdditive<T extends PsiAdditive>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - a type of the second operand at binary operation.
    All Superinterfaces:
    PsiConvertableToName, PsiConvertableToString, PsiObject
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    PsiArithmetic<T>, PsiNumeric, PsiRealNumeric
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PsiBigInteger, PsiComplex, PsiInteger, PsiPair, PsiReal

    public interface PsiAdditive<T extends PsiAdditive>
extends PsiObject
    A representation of Ψ-additive, a type of object that is an operand of arithmetic operation. This interface declares methods for addition, subtraction and negation.
